313
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:49,320
Hey, Misuzu...

314
00:16:49,940 --> 00:16:52,070
Was today not much fun for you?

315
00:16:52,820 --> 00:16:54,070
Bingo.

316
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:55,780
I see...

317
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:58,870
If I tried to spend time
with Tomo right now,

318
00:16:58,870 --> 00:17:02,750
I'd get exactly what I got from
these two days with Junichiro.

319
00:17:03,210 --> 00:17:06,170
There's just no hope for me.

320
00:17:06,170 --> 00:17:08,170
Hey, what's wrong with you?

321
00:17:08,170 --> 00:17:11,800
I thought you might be able
to do something about this...

322
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:16,890
But the way you are now, you're just
kicking her into higher gear.

323
00:17:18,550 --> 00:17:20,560
Hey, what's wrong, Misuzu?

324
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,310
You seem really down.

325
00:17:22,310 --> 00:17:24,100
Did something happen?

326
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:27,060
Yes. A lot happened.

327
00:17:27,810 --> 00:17:30,270
I'm sorry. I...

328
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:33,990
might not be able to keep being your friend.

329
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:35,700
Come on.

330
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:37,990
Ow! Hey!

331
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:41,700
Where are we going?
First period's about to start!

332
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,620
I don't care. Come with me.

333
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:47,420
What are you sulking about?

334
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:49,670
What do you mean, you can't
keep being my friend?

335
00:17:49,670 --> 00:17:50,790
I'll knock you out!

336
00:17:50,790 --> 00:17:52,210
That's extortion.

337
00:17:52,710 --> 00:17:55,300
I mean, I have no physical strength at all,

338
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:57,260
so I can't play sports with you or anything.

339
00:17:57,260 --> 00:17:58,680
What does that matter?!

340
00:17:59,050 --> 00:18:01,890
It's not like I'm running
around every single day!

341
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:05,850
Goofing around with the guys is fun,

342
00:18:05,850 --> 00:18:09,480
but the time I spend just being next
to you is way more precious to me.

343
00:18:09,860 --> 00:18:11,860
Are you saying you don't feel the same?

344
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:14,570
Where do you learn things like that?

345
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:17,320
What? Did I say something weird?

346
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:21,490
Why would it matter that much
whether you're athletic or not?

347
00:18:21,490 --> 00:18:23,160
I mean, like...

348
00:18:23,830 --> 00:18:24,830
Oh, yeah!

349
00:18:24,830 --> 00:18:29,210
Wouldn't it be cool for an athlete and
some kind of doctor to be friends?

350
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:34,210
What's "some kind of doctor"
supposed to mean?

351
00:18:34,630 --> 00:18:35,960
Don't laugh!

352
00:18:37,470 --> 00:18:40,720
All the things I was thinking
seem so silly now.

353
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:46,520
I guess going out with you
wasn't a total waste of time.

354
00:18:46,850 --> 00:18:48,310
So I'll at least...

355
00:18:48,980 --> 00:18:51,230
dump you soundly and completely.

356
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:53,110
Sorry, Misuzu.

357
00:18:53,110 --> 00:18:53,610
Huh?

358
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:58,240
I know this sounds weird when I'm
the one who asked you out, but...

359
00:18:58,240 --> 00:19:01,620
I feel like maybe we're not
a good match after all.

360
00:19:01,950 --> 00:19:05,410
So let's just give up on going out, okay?

361
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:10,420
He... beat me to it!

362
00:19:11,710 --> 00:19:13,840
Did you hear me? Hey, Misu—

363
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:16,840
Never... call me "Misuzu" again.

364
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:18,670
O-Okay.

365
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:22,640
I guess I'll have to handle this on my own.

366
00:19:24,010 --> 00:19:28,060
I'm scared to find out how she'll react
when I talk to her after all this time,

367
00:19:28,060 --> 00:19:29,770
but I'm prepared.

368
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:33,230
H-Hey, Tomo.

369
00:19:33,230 --> 00:19:35,820
I wanted to talk to you about something.

370
00:19:41,450 --> 00:19:44,580
I know I should be the one to talk first.

371
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:47,790
But what do I...

372
00:19:47,790 --> 00:19:50,000
Hey. Hey, Jun.

373
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:53,080
Can I just tell her how I really feel?

374
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,880
But if I tell her that...

375
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:56,300
I just said your name.

376
00:19:56,300 --> 00:19:59,340
Answer me, damn it!

377
00:20:02,930 --> 00:20:04,680
Where did that come f—

378
00:20:04,890 --> 00:20:10,140
Why did you just come up and
talk to me out of the blue?

379
00:20:10,140 --> 00:20:12,520
After you avoided me all this time...

380
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:14,940
For a whole year...

381
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:18,730
I-I'm sorry!

382
00:20:18,730 --> 00:20:21,450
It was my fault! Please don't cry!

383
00:20:21,450 --> 00:20:21,860
Huh?

384
00:20:22,530 --> 00:20:26,240
I'm not crying, you dumbass!

385
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:32,960
Why the hell were you avoiding
me all this time? Huh?!

386
00:20:33,210 --> 00:20:35,210
When the school year first started,

387
00:20:35,210 --> 00:20:40,420
people thought you and
I were... well... going out.

388
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:44,680
So I thought being around me would
just make things harder for you.

389
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:47,430
You were worried about
something that stupid?!

390
00:20:47,430 --> 00:20:48,060
Huh?

391
00:20:48,060 --> 00:20:51,430
If you and I both wanna be
together like we've always been,

392
00:20:51,430 --> 00:20:55,150
who the hell cares what anyone else thinks?!

393
00:20:56,270 --> 00:20:58,940
Well? What do you wanna do?

394
00:20:59,650 --> 00:21:00,990
I want...

395
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:05,610
to be with you. Just like we always have...

396
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:08,080
I wanna be like that forever!

397
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:15,670
S-So just be with me, then!

398
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:17,500
As f-friends!

399
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:20,880
Yeah! You and I are best buds forever!

400
00:21:21,380 --> 00:21:23,550
So let's have a lot more
good times together,

401
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:24,590
Tomo!

402
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:30,750
I thought we'd never change.

403
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:34,530
I thought it'd be best if we never changed.

404
00:21:35,730 --> 00:21:38,730
But then I changed.

405
00:21:38,730 --> 00:21:40,450
I think she has, too.

406
00:21:41,220 --> 00:21:46,650
So I have to think of a way
I can still be with her forever.

407
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:50,200
First of all, I have to face her head-on.

408
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,870
What's the hold-up, Jun?

409
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:54,070
C'mon, we gotta get to school!

410
00:21:55,490 --> 00:21:58,290
Face who Tomo is now head-on...

411
00:21:58,700 --> 00:22:00,420
Head-on...

412
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:04,450
I had a vague hunch it might be true,

413
00:22:04,450 --> 00:22:05,880
but isn't she actually...

414
00:22:06,270 --> 00:22:08,160
really cute?!

415
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:14,680
(This behavior is suspicious)

416
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:18,850
Hey, you know, I'm all mixed up

417
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:23,170
It's too complicated, I'm freaking out

418
00:22:23,490 --> 00:22:26,070
I can't figure out how to
say it, or how to read you

419
